Coming from one of the most recognised and reputed fashion brands Guess is this tastefully designed women’s personal timekeeper from its Mini Prism series of classic analog watches. As with most of the watches that come under the Mini Prism series this Guess analog watch too flaunts a lot of specific aesthetic elements that include high quality metallic finish and a generous measure of crystals or semi-precious stones. With such attention to detail this dazzling wristwatch from Guess is sure to keep you firmly in the gaze of all those around you.

The timekeeping function on this extremely elegant watch works on the popular quartz crystal technology which uses small bar shaped crystals of quartz. These quartz crystals work by generating an electrical charge which causes them to vibrate at a thousand times a second making them extremely stable resonators for extremely accurate timekeeping. One of the biggest advantages of employing this quartz crystal technology apart from its operational accuracy is the cost effective nature of the entire manufacturing process.

Body & Design

This artistically crafted watch sports a round dial that measures 35 mm in diameter with a 12 mm thickness while also sporting an extensive amount of crystal stone work surrounding it. This highly aesthetic dial has a considerable circle of protection in the form of a sturdy and durable stainless steel case. The bezel which forms the upper portion of this stainless steel case is given the full treatment with an assortment of crystals that is a sure eye-catcher with its undeniable brilliance.

The watch’s stone-studded dial contains a watch face with a light solid colour as the background. The outer ring of the watch face has contrasting dark coloured minute markings while the numerical hour markers have a brilliant metallic finish which is very similar to the rest of the watch. The dial further sports two sub-dials that further increase the functionality of this masterpiece of a watch.

The time indicating hands on the dial also have the same metallic colour with a sufficient amount of luminescent material in them. This luminescent material in the watch hands gives them the highly useful afterglow ability which allows you to read the time even in absolute darkness. All these well planned colour combinations within the dial lets you easily differentiate between the various elements on the dial leading to effortless and hassle-free time reading.

The watch’s round dial with its glamorous stone set arrangement is kept safely and securely attached to your wrist at ball times with the help of its gleaming stainless steel bracelet strap. This strap can be easily fastened and unfastened by using its stylish and effective fold-over clasp.

Functions and Other Features

The two sub-dials located at the 12 and 6 o’clock positions are the day and date indicators respectively. All the time date and day displayed on the dial can be adjusted or changed with the easy operation of the watch’s rotating crown which is placed on the right of the dial’s case.
